mugginsville2000:
You can delete the .torrent file you downloaded. As long as the .torrent file is active in your Torrent client, it will keep uploading, provided you did not move any of the files from their download directory.
(If you do move them, you will need to specify the new location for the client for it to seed, in its complete state. For example if it was a folder with several files in it, you need to keep the folder intact as it is, to be able to seed from it)

how do increase my bittorrent speed?
how do i make bittorrent faster???

For those asking how to make the torrent speed faster -- Be sure not to leave your upload speed set to unlimited is the main thing I have found that speeds things up !! -- leave around 15 - 20% of your max speed unused for uploading ( Having it set to unlimited will cause slowdowns as the downloads speed increases due to the overhead that is needed to maintain all of the connections and send requests for pieces.) having it set to unlimited will quickly have the torrent program maxing the available upload bandwidth and there will not be enough for your system to maintain the connections with others and request pieces for download slowing the download speed. --- you want to share by uploading but in order to get a good download speed you need to cap the upload to about 80-85% of your capacity to allow the connections to be maintained without effecting performance.

Also while doing this set your max upload connections to a reasonable amount depending on your connection speed so that each connection you make will be given more but you'll have fewer connections to maintain ( ie. if your upload speed is set to say 500KB\s limit upload connections to say 50 or so -- that way you will only be uploading to 50 others but will be giving an average of 10KB\s to each instead of having 500 connections to upload to but only giving 1KB\s to each one. (this will also help download speed since 50 connections takes less overhead than 500 !)

Or...have an old machine running linux as your downloader. I have an old P4 in the laundry room with a 32gb SD stickin out of it. The distro is trimmed down for the sole purpose of bittorrent downloading....very fast as nothing else is accessing the net. Take the card out and dump on my big machine. I have the upload set to 50% of potential.
